## Quick start

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# fill in secrets
npm install
npm run build
npm start
```

{{#if useSqlDatabase}}
{{#if (eq sqlBootstrap "docker_postgres")}}
## Local Postgres (Docker)

If you do not already have a database, start the bundled Postgres:

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

Ensure `{{{databaseUrlEnvVar}}}` in `.env` matches [docker-compose.yml](docker-compose.yml) (default in `.env.example`: `postgres://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/agent`).
{{/if}}
{{#if (eq sqlBootstrap "sqlite_file")}}
## Local SQLite

No database server required. The app opens `SQLITE_PATH` (default `{{{sqliteFilePath}}}`); parent folders are created automatically.
{{/if}}
{{#if (eq sqlBootstrap "connection_url")}}
## Database connection

Set `{{{databaseUrlEnvVar}}}` in `.env` to your existing Postgres (or compatible) URL.
{{/if}}
{{/if}}

## Layout

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/agents/` | Orchestration for the selected design pattern |
| `src/tools/` | Tool definitions (AI SDK) |
| `src/memory/` | Memory backends |
| `src/prompts/` | System / assistant instructions |
| `src/knowledge/` | Knowledge & vector stubs |
| `src/llm/` | Provider model factory (Vercel AI SDK) |
| `agent.scaffold.json` | Exact answers from the TUI wizard |

